.SH NAME
Linux::Event::Proactor::Backend::Uring \- io_uring backend for Linux::Event::Proactor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 5
\&  # Usually constructed internally by Linux::Event::Proactor.
\&  my $loop = Linux::Event::Loop\->new(
\&    model   => \*(Aqproactor\*(Aq,
\&    backend => \*(Aquring\*(Aq,
\&  );
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\f(CW\*(C`Linux::Event::Proactor::Backend::Uring\*(C'\fR is the completion backend for
Linux::Event::Proactor. It submits reads, writes, socket operations, timers,
and cancellation requests through IO::Uring.
.PP
The backend preserves the core proactor invariants by leaving user callback
execution to the engine. It records pending operations, normalizes completion
results, and settles user\-visible operations through the owning loop.
.PP
Multishot accept is used internally to service ordinary one\-shot public
\&\f(CWaccept()\fR requests.
.PP
When configured provided\-buffer fast\-path conditions are met, ordinary one\-shot
public \f(CWrecv()\fR requests may also be serviced internally by a shared
multishot receive source while still preserving single\-settlement public
operation semantics.
.SH "CONSTRUCTOR OPTIONS"
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR OPTIONS"
The backend is normally constructed internally. Recognized options include:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`submit_batch_size\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Optional submission batching threshold. When non\-zero, the backend flushes the
ring after this many queued submissions.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`cqe_entries\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Optional \f(CW\*(C`IO::Uring\*(C'\fR completion queue size tuning.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`sqpoll\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Optional \f(CW\*(C`IO::Uring\*(C'\fR SQPOLL mode toggle.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`provided_buffer_size\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Optional global provided\-buffer size for the internal multishot recv fast path.
Defaults to 4096.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`provided_buffer_count\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Optional global provided\-buffer count for the internal multishot recv fast
path. Defaults to 512.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`provided_buffer_group\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Optional global provided\-buffer group id. Defaults to 0.
.SH "SUPPORTED OPERATIONS"
.IX Header "SUPPORTED OPERATIONS"
This backend currently implements:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`read\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`write\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`splice\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`recv\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`send\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`accept\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`connect\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`shutdown\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`close\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`after\*(C'\fR / \f(CW\*(C`at\*(C'\fR via internal timeout submission
.IP \(bu 4
cancellation of submitted operations
.SH NOTES
.IX Header "NOTES"
The backend is intentionally low\-level and is not expected to be used
directly by most applications.
